Gov. Bello Matawalle of Zamfara has approved the constitution of a 9-man Negotiation Committee on the N30,000 Minimum Wage. This was contained in a statement signed by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Alhaji Bala Maru and made available to journalists in Gusau on Wednesday. Maru said that the committee was mandated to fashion out modalities on how workers in the state will benefit from the new minimum wage. He said Alhaji Bashir Yuguda, a former Minister of Finance would serve as the chairman of the committee. Maru said that membership of the committee included Permanent Secretaries, labour unions among others. He, however, did not give the duration of the committee’s work Vanguard News Nigeria Secretary to the Government of Zamfara State, SSG, Alhaji Bala Maru, has reiterated the state government's determination to bring an end to banditry and insecurity bedevilling the state. June 17, 2019 In "News" The Oyo State Chapter of Nigeria labour Congress(NLC) and Trade Union Congress (TUC) in the state said the N18,000 minimum wage cannot withstand economy of the nation any longer and recommend N66,500 minimum wage for workers. April 27, 2018 In "News" THE workers’ long journey to the N18,000 minimum wage, which the Senate passed into law on Tuesday, February 22, started long before the late President Musa Yar’Adua, on July 14, 2009, through the then Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Alhaji Mahmud Yayale Ahmed, inaugurated a tripartite Presidential Committee… February 27, 2011 In "Special Report"